CNCP v1 22918
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5579: a component that passes slots to children forces children to rerender",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:34.497645+00:00",
  "text": "a component that passes slots to children forces children to rerender\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.31\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[github.com](https://github.com/Gagydzer/vue-slots-rerender-bug)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nI've found some cases that shouldn't makes slot-component to update, but it does. Only case #1 works properly. It looks like a bug, because it affects at lot of cases when you want to pass slots through a component to a children with this technique.\r\n\r\n```\r\nVue.component('W', {\r\n  props: ['child'],\r\n  template: `<component :is=\"child\">\r\n  <template v-for=\"(_, name) in $slots\" v-slot:[name]=\"slotData\"><slot :name=\"name\" v-bind=\"slotData\" /></template>\r\n</component>`\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nno updates in children component\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nit does update\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "need guidance",
    "scope: slots"
  ],
